---
/**
 * dl-item Custom Element Documentation
 *
 * Groups a dt/dd pair within a description list for styling purposes.
 */
import ElementLayout from '../../../../layouts/ElementLayout.astro';

// Code examples as template strings
const basicUsageCode = `<dl class="key-value">
  <dl-item>
    <dt>Full Name</dt>
    <dd>Alexandra Chen</dd>
  </dl-item>

  <dl-item>
    <dt>Email</dt>
    <dd>alexandra.chen@example.com</dd>
  </dl-item>

  <dl-item>
    <dt>Status</dt>
    <dd>Active</dd>
  </dl-item>
</dl>`;

const horizontalLayoutCode = `@scope (.key-value) {
  dl-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
    gap: var(--size-m);
    align-items: baseline;
    padding-block: var(--size-s);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  dl-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
}`;

const stackedLayoutCode = `@scope (.key-value[data-layout="stacked"]) {
  dl-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--size-2xs);
  }
}`;

const cssImplementation = `dl-item {
  display: block;
}`;

const multipleValuesCode = `<dl class="key-value">
  <dl-item>
    <dt>Phone Numbers</dt>
    <dd>+1 (555) 123-4567</dd>
    <dd>+1 (555) 987-6543</dd>
  </dl-item>
</dl>`;
---

<ElementLayout
  title="dl-item"
  description="Groups a dt/dd pair within a description list for styling purposes."
  elementName="dl-item"
  category="custom"
  currentPath="/docs/elements/custom-elements/dl-item/"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> custom element is a structural wrapper that groups a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a>/<a href="/docs/elements/native/dd/"><code>&lt;dd&gt;</code></a> pair within a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> (description list). It exists purely for styling purposes, enabling grid and flex layouts that treat each term-description pair as a unit.</p>
    <p>This element has no semantic meaning itself—it simply provides a styling hook that the native HTML structure lacks. The <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> element allows <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrappers for this purpose, and custom elements work the same way.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Inside <code>&lt;dl class="key-value"&gt;</code> description lists</li>
      <li>When you need horizontal (grid) or stacked (flex) layouts for term-description pairs</li>
      <li>With <code>@scope</code> CSS rules that target the key-value pattern</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Outside of a <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li>For basic description lists that don't need row-based styling</li>
      <li>When the default indented <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> styling is sufficient</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>Wrap each <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pair in a <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> element within a description list.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <dl class="key-value">
        <dl-item>
          <dt>Full Name</dt>
          <dd>Alexandra Chen</dd>
        </dl-item>

        <dl-item>
          <dt>Email</dt>
          <dd>alexandra.chen@example.com</dd>
        </dl-item>

        <dl-item>
          <dt>Status</dt>
          <dd>Active</dd>
        </dl-item>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic dl-item usage">{basicUsageCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multiple Values</h2>
    <p>A single <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> can contain one <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> with multiple <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements for terms that have several values.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <dl class="key-value">
        <dl-item>
          <dt>Phone Numbers</dt>
          <dd>+1 (555) 123-4567</dd>
          <dd>+1 (555) 987-6543</dd>
        </dl-item>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Multiple values in one dl-item">{multipleValuesCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Implementation</h2>
    <p>The base element is simply a block container:</p>

    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="dl-item base styles">{cssImplementation}</code-block>

    <p>The actual layout styling is applied via <code>@scope</code> rules that target the <code>.key-value</code> pattern class.</p>

    <h3>Horizontal Layout</h3>
    <p>For side-by-side label-value display:</p>

    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Horizontal layout with @scope">{horizontalLayoutCode}</code-block>

    <h3>Stacked Layout</h3>
    <p>For vertical stacking with label above value:</p>

    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Stacked layout with @scope">{stackedLayoutCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why a Custom Element?</h2>
    <p>Using <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> instead of <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> provides several benefits:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Semantic clarity:</strong> The element name describes its purpose—grouping a description list item</li>
      <li><strong>Targeted styling:</strong> CSS selectors like <code>dl-item</code> are more specific than <code>div</code></li>
      <li><strong>Pattern recognition:</strong> Easy to identify key-value patterns in the HTML</li>
      <li><strong>No JavaScript required:</strong> The element works as a pure styling hook</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Note: HTML5 explicitly allows wrapping <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pairs in <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> elements, and custom elements inherit this behavior.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Model</h2>

    <h3>Permitted Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>One or more <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements</li>
      <li>One or more <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements</li>
      <li>The <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements should come before <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Required Parent</h3>
    <p>Must be a direct child of <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> - Description list container (required parent)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a> - Definition term (the key/label)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dd/"><code>&lt;dd&gt;</code></a> - Definition description (the value)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Patterns Using This Element</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code> element is designed specifically for these patterns:</p>
    <layout-grid data-min="200px" data-gap="m">
      <a href="/docs/patterns/data/description-list/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Key-Value / Description List</h3>
        <p>Display key-value pairs in horizontal or stacked layouts</p>
      </a>
    </layout-grid>
  </section>
</ElementLayout>
